  "text": "Moreels and Perona [CITATION_1] have previously developed a correspondence evaluation scheme for full 3D scenes. Their scheme geometrically verifies matches between corresponding points in two views of a scene using an additional auxiliary view. While this setup guarantees that almost no false matches are let through, it has the disadvantage that only features visible in all three views can be checked. Furthermore, their use of point correspondences implicitly discourages matching of large regions, since these are represented by the region centroid, which is only affine invariant, with an error that increases with the region size.",
